cloud service offerings :

Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS)
What it is: Renting raw infrastructure (servers, storage, networking) from a cloud provider.

You manage: OS, runtime, applications.

Example in GCP: Compute Engine (virtual machines).

pay for what they allocate

⚙️ Platform as a Service (PaaS)
What it is: A ready‑made platform to build and deploy apps without worrying about infrastructure.

You manage: Just your application code.

Example in GCP: App Engine (deploy code, Google handles scaling and runtime).

pay for what they use

serverless cloud computing
PaaS: Always-on platform, you deploy apps and the platform manages them.
Serverless: Event-driven, runs only when needed, scales instantly to zero when idle.

🖥️ Software as a Service (SaaS)
What it is: Fully managed software delivered over the internet.

You manage: Nothing — you just use the software.

Example in GCP: Google Workspace (Docs, Gmail, Sheets).

